# AWS SNS Verifier Project Structure

This is a Python library for verifying AWS SNS signatures. The main components are:

- **Core validation**: [src/aws_sns_verifier/validator.py](mdc:src/aws_sns_verifier/validator.py) - Main signature validation logic
- **Data models**: [src/aws_sns_verifier/models.py](mdc:src/aws_sns_verifier/models.py) - Pydantic models for SNS messages
- **Email handling**: [src/aws_sns_verifier/attachments.py](mdc:src/aws_sns_verifier/attachments.py) - Email attachment extraction
- **Package config**: [pyproject.toml](mdc:pyproject.toml) - Project dependencies and configuration

## Architecture Principles

- Uses Pydantic models for all data validation and type safety
- Follows AWS SNS documentation standards exactly
- Cryptographic operations use the `cryptography` library
- All functions include comprehensive type hints
- Error handling uses descriptive exception messages